goal: exists(k0: Real) { double_converges(f) implies double_converges_to(f, k0) }
proof: let s0: ((Nat, Nat) -> Real) -> Real satisfy { forall(x0: (Nat, Nat) -> Real) { not double_converges(x0) or double_converges_to(x0, s0(x0)) } and forall(x1: (Nat, Nat) -> Real, x2: Real) { not double_converges_to(x1, x2) or double_converges(x1) } }
